            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "First, place bacon on a baking sheet lined with foil paper and bake at 400F for 10 min or until crispy texture, after finely chop bacon into tiny pieces for garnish & set aside."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "While bacon is baking, peel and slice 5 lb potatoes and place them into a big pot. Cover potatoes with water and bring them to a boil. After the potatoes start boiling, reduce the heat to medium/high and cook for about 10-15 minutes or until potatoes turn soft when inserted with a knife."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 350 F."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Drain water and place potato in a big mixing bowl. Now add 3/4 cup sour cream, 1 cup milk, 5 tablespoons of butter, salt and pepper to taste. Blend with a blender until fluffy texture."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Using a spatula, fold in 2 cups of cheese, then transfer potatoes to a casserole dish, top with 1 cup of shredded cheese and bake uncovered at 350 F for 30 minutes or until heated thru."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Garnish potato casserole with crumbled bacon pieces and finely chopped fresh chives. Enjoy!"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Making ahead - Make this potato casserole ahead by following step 1-3, then cover the casserole and place it in the fridge until you are ready to bake it.  About 30 minutes before serving follow steps 4-5."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
